 Collision detection logic in /root/snake-game/snake_game/core/:

  Wall Collisions (snake_game.py:66-70):
  - Snake.check_collision() tests if head.x < 0 or head.x >= grid_size (left/right edges)
  - Same for head.y (top/bottom)
  - Returns True immediately on any boundary breach
  - In SnakeGame.move_snake() (snake_game.py:181-189), this triggers game-over unless invincible power-up is active

  Self Collisions (snake_game.py:72-74):
  - head in self.body[1:] checks if head position matches any body segment after the head
  - Returns True for self-collision 
  - In move_snake(), ghost mode (can_pass_self) allows the check to pass silently (snake_game.py:185-186)
  - Otherwise sets game_running = False

  Food Collection (snake_game.py:191-197):
  - SnakeGame checks snake.get_head() == food.get_position() after movement
  - Equality uses Point.__eq__ which compares x/y values
  - On match: snake.grow() (increments grow_segments), award 10 × points_multiplier, increment combo counter, call power_up_manager.on_food_collected()
  - generate_food() ensures new food never spawns on snake.body or bonus_food.position
  - Food collection does not trigger collision detection; the head simply occupies the same cell

  All collision checks run in the main loop after snake.move() and before the next frame. Power-ups can suppress or modify outcomes.
